<br>
I would recommend the following:<br>
<br>
1. Run all tests at 200 INT/WIS since this can easily be achieved without mind buffs but is still enough mana pool to cast quite a few spells.<br>
<br>
2. Run all test with no buffs at all, standing the entire time. This is because at 1 mana/tick there is a lot less variance caused by hitting the mana regen tick and possible wrong mana regen number totals.<br>
<br>
3. Run the test with 2 different set ups. One where you cas a higher level higher mana spell until you can't cast then switching to a very low level spell to oom and one where you cast only a low level spell to oom. When you finally get to insufficient mana to cast the low level spell you should stand chain clicking the low level spell until it casts so you can be sure you are totally oom.<br>
<br>
4. All tests with fizzles should be discarded and rerun.<br>
<br>
I would think we would need a sample size of at least 1000 bars of mana to account for irregularities and VI's wonderful RNG.<br>
<br>
I will head to Tox tonight and run a few bars of mana down to see what I come up with with SCM0.<br>
<br>
