<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Pre-SCM 200 Specialization Test</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Standing regen: 1<br>
Epic regen: 3<br>
Went completely oom by casting 8 mana spell till oom then one more time to make sure was completely oom.<br>
From oom to 75 mana took 19 ticks, repeated this test three times.  (was using Flame Shock I think)<br>
Subsequent casts of the 75 mana spell took 17 ticks.  Repeated this test twenty times.<br>
Mana saved: 75/(4*2)~10%.<br>
<br>
In other words, my 200 specialization in evocation went off every single time I cast the spell and reduced the mana cost by 10%.<br>
<br>
The AA description sounds like a dangling participle in that it sounds like it will increase the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> chance</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> by 5, 15, or 30%.  The chance of a 200 specialzation going off is 100%, so this interpretation would only help 50 spec skills.<br>
<br>
It's possible that SCM adds some unknown chance for the mana saved to be above the minimum 10%, ie 15%, 25%, or 40% mana saved.  This would actually make more sense because the description above is bad English... Only someone with SCM3 could try to figure out what the unknown chance is and if it always saves either the minimum 10% or 40%... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukitiari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kitiari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/18/02 2:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My hopes are dashed... but maybe not...</span><hr size=1> It doesn't save you 10% every cast.  This is easy to prove when you are LOM and trying to cast a spell but dont have the mana then after clicking a couple more times spec kicks in and you cast. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utwiddleotoole.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiddle OToole</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_bullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Arrrrghh!!! Ahoy!</span><br>  Posts: 740<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/18/02 2:18 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/twidsm2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My hopes are dashed... but maybe not...</span><hr size=1> Hm, of interest here is that this skill effectively improves two things, if it works as we suspect.  On the one hand, it reduces mana cost, which effectively gives us a larger mana pool when FoM, thereby allowing us to nuke more on a full bar.  But that larger mana pool doesn't take any longer to regenerate, so we're also effectively increasing mana regeneration speed.<br>
<br>
In short:  x% larger mana pool, x% faster regen.<br>
<br>
Come to think of it, this also applies to SCF criticals, which have the added advantage of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> creating x% more aggro.<br>
